properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued March 2 at 3:35AM PST until March 2 at 6:00PM PST by NWS Sacramento CA
properties.description:
...Windy today across portions of interior Northern California...

.Strong high pressure building inland will result in windy
conditions across northern and western portions of Sacramento
Valley today, extending into the Coastal Range, and in the Delta
area. Strongest wind expected this afternoon.

* WHAT...North winds 20 to 30 mph with gusts to around 40 mph
expected.

* WHERE...Carquinez Strait and Delta County.

* WHEN...From 7 AM this morning to 6 PM PST this evening.

* IMPACTS...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects.
Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may
result.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Fuels are at record low levels for this
time of year. Use extreme caution with ignition sources and any
outdoor burning..
properties.instruction:
Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high
profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 7 AM THIS MORNING TO 6 PM PST THIS EVENING
